{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GNRFLRjXaZKx9V7JC53Yt1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The second raylet started when `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')` was called (at 18:24:17). The raylet started, but immediately the dashboard_agent and runtime_env_agent failed with \"exit code -1\". This caused the raylet to self-terminate.\n\nThe error: \"The agent failed to start because of unexpected error or port conflict.\"\n\nThe first `ray start` (at 18:21:38) left behind some running processes (log_monitor is still running as we saw). These processes might be holding ports that the second raylet needs.\n\nWhen `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')` was called, it created a new raylet in the SAME session directory (session_2026-06-14_18-19-10_149278_11). \n\nThe second raylet crashed likely because the log_monitor from the first session survived the `ray stop` command and is still holding ports that the dashboard_agent and runtime_env_agent need. I should check those agent logs to see what the actual port conflict is.\n\nThe solution is to do a complete cleanup: kill all ray processes, remove the /tmp/ray directory, and start fresh with `ray start --address=ray-head:6379`. But I'm wondering if this cleanup can run in the pod and whether a fresh start will actually resolve the conflicts, or if the second `ray start` at 18:24:09 just appeared to succeed when it actually didn't.\n\nLooking at the raylet logs more carefully, the first `ray start` spawned raylet PID 103, but the second attempt created raylet PID 297 which started up and then crashed shortly after. The timing suggests `ray start` exits before the raylet fully stabilizes, which is why the crash happens after the command completes. So the raylet that started at 18:24:09 must have crashed within seconds, clearing the sockets by the time `ray.init()` ran at 18:24:17. When `ray.init()` tried to start a replacement raylet, it also failed—this time because the agents (dashboard_agent and runtime_env_agent) couldn't initialize properly.\n\nNow I need to look at what actually went wrong with those agents.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1889,"cache_read_input_tokens":62944,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1889},"output_tokens":17,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5492027-9e24-4f6a-adc0-2a43726cf418","uuid":"59c88fcb-945a-4d03-b81b-f45f42ae8200","request_id":"req_011Cc4AzkTmxjmq2Mt3DZsjP"}
